# Netscape HTTP Cookie File
# This file is used by yt-dlp to access YouTube
# =============================================================================
# WHY YOU NEED THIS:
# YouTube has anti-bot measures that block automated downloads.
# Without cookies, you may see errors like:
# "Sign in to confirm you're not a bot"
# =============================================================================
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR COOKIES:
#
# Method 1: Using a browser extension (Recommended)
# 1. Install "Get cookies.txt LOCALLY" extension (Chrome/Firefox/Edge)
#    - Chrome: https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/get-cookiestxt-locally/cclelndahbckbenkjhflpdbgdldlbecc
#    - Firefox: https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/cookies-txt/
# 2. Go to YouTube.com and make sure you're logged in
# 3. Click the extension icon in your browser toolbar
# 4. Click "Export" or "Current Tab"
# 5. Save the file as "cookies.txt" (without the .example extension)
#
# Method 2: Using yt-dlp directly from browser
# Run: yt-dlp --cookies-from-browser chrome --cookies cookies.txt "https://youtube.com"
# This exports cookies directly from your browser to a file.
#
# Method 3: Manual export using browser developer tools
# 1. Open YouTube in your browser while logged in
# 2. Press F12 to open developer tools
# 3. Go to Application > Cookies > https://www.youtube.com
# 4. Export cookies in Netscape format using a tool
#
# =============================================================================
# FORMAT EXAMPLE:
# =============================================================================
# .youtube.com    TRUE    /    FALSE    1234567890    VISITOR_INFO1_LIVE    XXXXXX
# .youtube.com    TRUE    /    FALSE    1234567890    PREF    XXXXXX
# .youtube.com    TRUE    /    TRUE    1234567890    SID    XXXXXX
#
# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# =============================================================================
# - Rename this file to "cookies.txt" to use it (remove .example extension)
# - Keep your cookies file SECURE - never share it or commit it to git!
# - Cookies expire periodically - re-export if downloads start failing
# - Add cookies.txt to .gitignore to prevent accidental commits
# - For Docker, mount the cookies file: -v /path/to/cookies.txt:/app/cookies.txt
#
# =============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING:
# =============================================================================
# If downloads still fail after adding cookies:
# 1. Make sure the cookies file is recent (not expired)
# 2. Try logging out and back into YouTube, then re-export cookies
# 3. Check that your account doesn't have restrictions
# 4. Try using a different YouTube account
# 5. Check the yt-dlp version: pip show yt-dlp
#    If outdated, update: pip install -U yt-dlp
